'Part' may refer to: *Part (haircut) *Part (mathematics), a relation in
mereology *Part (music), the music played or sung by an individual instrument or
voice *''Parts'' (book), a 1997 children's book by Tedd Arnold *Parts book : a
'parts book' or 'parts catalogue' is a book published by manufacturers which
contains the part numbers and other relevant data for their products or parts
thereof. *Pärt Uusberg (born 1986), Estonian composer and conductor *Arvo Pärt
(born 1935), Estonian classical composer *John Part (born 1966), Canadian darts
player *Spare part, a component kept for replacement of other failed components

*Program Assessment Review Tool, United States federal funding assessment *PART,
an acronym for the Putnam Transit bus system *PART, an acronym for the Pottstown
Area Rapid Transit
